This sample shows how populate a UltraTree from a ProBindingSource control, and how to synchronize the UltraTree control with the ProBindingSource control. This synchronization allows both controls to be repositioned when the other changes the selected record.

The Form1_Load event set up all the bindings and navigation options for the Employee and Family UltraTree controls.
The UltraTree SynchronizeCurrencyManager property is set to TRUE in order to allow synchronization between the UltraTree and the ProBindingSource controls.
 
